title: Cover-up? NASA Cuts Live Feed From ISS as ‘Object Hundreds of Miles Long’ Spotted
text:
Total:
Cover-up? NASA Cuts Live Feed From ISS as ‘Object Hundreds of Miles Long’ Spotted
Tuesday, January 23, 2018 15:02
% of readers think this story is Fact. Add your two cents.
Could this be the evidence needed to prove NASA is covering up the existence of UFOs and extraterrestrial life?  Some seem to think so, as the space agency mysteriously cut the International Space Station’s live feed not long after a massive object hundreds of miles long was spotted above Earth.
The footage, taken from a live stream from the International Space Station, a bright golden light is seen “over 200 miles” away from the camera.  It remains in the same place as the ISS orbits around the Earth but before viewers see any more of the mystery object, the video is cut.
Scott Brando, a UFO hoax investigator who runs ufoointerest.org , told  Express.co.uk : “I think this is a reflection of sunlight through clouds.” But many aren’t convinced.  And if all it was was a bit of sunlight through some clouds, why did NASA cut the live feed?
StreetCap1 posted the below video on YouTube:
StreetCap1 captioned the video. He says on YouTube, “I thought I was seeing things at first then quickly started recording. To my surprise, they cut the [sic] transmission. This has to be huge whatever it is. If it was a building it would be hundreds of miles long.”
Could it be a UFO? Did NASA cut the feed on purpose? Is it a reflection of light? Is it a coincidence?  It’s probably best to use your imagination because we likely won’t get the truth out of the government (NASA) even if it is, indeed, an extraterrestrial spacecraft.
